cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.RO 

Reasoning: 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on developing a driver model that captures human driving behavior and can be utilized by semi- and fully autonomous systems. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes using classification tools to build the driver model and mentions developing human-inspired safety metrics for intelligent vehicular systems. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper discusses using multiple algorithms to build the driver model and achieving high accuracy in identifying driver intent. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is mentioned as a feature used in building the driver model based on the driver's perception of the environment. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the use of the driver model in autonomous systems.
